"color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: A feature request, i.e: not implemented / a PR."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 9, "created_at": "2019-09-24T05:59:26Z", "updated_at": "2020-10-05T01:40:50Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "If you have a `Vec<u8>` of utf8 data there's three ways to get a `String`:\r\n\r\n* `from_utf8(vec: Vec<u8>) -> Result<String, FromUtf8Error>`\r\n* `from_utf8_lossy(v: &'a [u8]) -> Cow<'a, str>`\r\n* `unsafe fn from_utf8_unchecked(bytes: Vec<u8>) -> String`\r\n\r\nThere doesn't appear to be any way to hand over the existing `Vec<u8>` and have any necessary character changes into `\ufffd` be done _in place_. The `std::string::FromUtf8Error` type doesn't, for example, have a way to just do a lossy in-place conversion.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/64727/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/64727/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}